problems: High network congestion with 12 total networks present.
Multiple overlapping channels causing interference, particularly on 2.4GHz.
Weak signal quality on 5GHz due to noise and competition.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to channel 1 for less congestion, as channels 11 and 1 are already overcrowded.
Change the 5GHz channel to channel 149 for optimal performance, avoiding congested channels 36 and 44.
Consider relocating the router away from the bedroom window to a more central location in the home to improve coverage.
If available, enable Smart Connect to automatically manage device connections for optimal band usage.
Minimize interference from devices that may operate on the same frequency bands.
